===Noun===
# '''Dyirbal''' is an [[w:Ergative-absolutive language|ergative]] [[w:Australian Aboriginal languages|Australian Aboriginal language]] of the [[w:Dyirbalic languages|Dyirbalic]] branch of the [[w:Pama-Nyungan languages|Pama-Nyungan]] family. In 2001, only about five speakers remained in northeastern [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].

